#    feature mismatches. It dynamically identifies numeric/categorical columns to handle unknown schemas.
# 4. Energy Efficiency: Avoided PCA and large ensembles. For the NSL-KDD dataset, a shallow tree provides a 
#    diminishing-returns trade-off that favors CPU conservation.
# 5. Data Safety: Included checks for empty datasets and coerced numeric types to prevent runtime crashes.
